race.comment: JELLICIOUS (2) snagged back from the wide draw and never in the contest when a plugging sixth over 1300m at Randwick in this class. Gets the right set-up here and can tag the good tempo. WEEPING WOMAN (1) heavily supported into favouritism on resumption when raced handy for a dominant win over 1100m at Rosehill. Goes equally as well second-up but will have to do a bit of work early to get across. Sure to be thereabouts. SPIRIT OF WEALTH (7) slow into stride from the sticky draw and charged late when taking ground off WEEPING WOMAN. Strips fitter and worth noting Berry hops off to ride JELLICIOUS. Stays in the mix. MADRINA (5) racing in good order in easier company and brings a solid set of figures here. Blinkers go on and shapes a value chance. AMREEKIYAH (8) never comfortable on the rain affected tracks in stronger grade last preparation. Fitted with the one trial and undefeated first-up.
